"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819133","Department for Education","false","2018-01-15","<p>Universities are autonomous institutions and they are responsible for their own pension provision. The department has not taken steps to encourage Universities UK, or any other party, to resolve the dispute regarding the Universities Superannuation Scheme, but continues to monitor developments.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819133/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T16:31:05.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819133/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819133/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-09","Universities Superannuation Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps his Department has taken to encourage Universities UK to resolve the dispute over the Universities Superannuation Scheme.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","121810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819134","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-15","<p>An estimated 80 per cent of personnel who left the Armed Forces in Financial Year (FY) 2015-16 were employed six months after leaving their Service. The Ministry of Defence is due to publish updated statistics (for FY 2016-17 Service leavers) on Thursday 25 January. Full details of the current statistics can be found at the following address:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/career-transition-partnership-ex-service-personnel-employment-outcomes-statistics-index.</p><p>Employment rates for veterans at the one year and five year points after leaving the Armed Forces are not held by the Ministry of Defence.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819134/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:42:11.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819134/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819134/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-09","Veterans: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent estimate his Department has made of the employment levels of veterans (a) 6 months, (b) one year and (c) five years after leaving the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","121811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819135","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-15","<p>The letter sent by the Minister of State on 12 December to the Hon. Member for Sunderland Central and the Hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland outlined the improvements being made to the court estate in Sunderland.</p><p> </p><p>The decision to integrate court and tribunal sites in Sunderland into the Magistrates’ Court building will enable us to focus investment into a single building in Sunderland. This will result in a better standard of accommodation and improve the experience of those who use the court.</p><p> </p><p>I am still considering future meetings and visits but in the meantime, I would be happy to consider any comments the Hon. Member may have regarding these plans through correspondence.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819135/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:55:57.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819135/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819135/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-09","Courts: Sunderland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will meet the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland and the hon. Member for Sunderland Central to discuss the future of the Sunderland Court Estate.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","121812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819136","Prime Minister","false","2018-01-15","<p>Ministerial salaries are published online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministerial-salary-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministerial-salary-data</a></p><p>Across each level of responsibility, male and female Ministers are paid the same.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819136/answer",,,,,"121814","2018-01-15T16:43:25.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819136/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819136/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2018-01-09","Ministers: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what the average salary is of (a) men and (b) women attending the Cabinet since the reshuffle on 8 January 2017.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","121813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819137","Prime Minister","false","2018-01-15","<p>Ministerial salaries are published online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministerial-salary-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministerial-salary-data</a></p><p>Across each level of responsibility, male and female Ministers are paid the same.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819137/answer",,,,,"121813","2018-01-15T16:43:26.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819137/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819137/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2018-01-09","Ministers: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what the average salary is for (a) men and (b) women in the Government following the reshuffle of 8 and 9 January 2017.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","121814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819138","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-02-09","<p>The government is supportive of more recycling of materials and we are actively engaged in agreeing the proposals to support the Circular Economy across the EU. We are yet to receive the formal text of the outcome of the trilogue discussions and we will consider it carefully. There are several targets in the circular economy package of which the 65% recycling by weight target by 2035 is just one.</p><p> </p><p>As we develop the Resource and Waste Strategy we will explore whether new, more innovate targets can be developed that deliver clear benefits over those proposed by Europe. Should they be preferable, UK Government will present proposals to the UK Parliament following the UKs Exit from Europe.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819138/answer",,,,,,"2018-02-09T13:54:38.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819138/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819138/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-01-09","Recycling: EU Action","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the Government’s policy is on the proposed common EU target to recycle 65 per cent of municipal waste by 2035.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","121815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819139","Department for Education","false","2018-01-17","<p>In the speech which resulted in this article, my Rt hon. Friend the Minister of State for Universities, Science, Research and Innovation gave two distinct examples of threats to freedom of speech – the removal of ‘offensive’ material from libraries, and the drawing up of lists of ‘trigger words’. He did not state that books were being removed due to the inclusion of trigger words.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819139/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T17:13:22.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819139/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819139/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-09","Universities: Libraries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to Guardian article published on 26 December 2017, entitled Jo Johnson to tell universities to stop no-platforming speakers, which universities have removed books from university libraries due to the inclusion of trigger words.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","121816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819140","Prime Minister","false","2018-01-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the press release issued on 9 January following the reshuffle and which is available on the gov.uk website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/ministerial-appointments-january-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/ministerial-appointments-january-2018</a></p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819140/answer",,,,,"121819","2018-01-15T16:42:35.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819140/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819140/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2018-01-09","Ministers: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, how many unpaid members of her Government are (a) men and (b) women.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","121817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819141","Department for International Trade","false","2018-01-17","<p>All the countries which currently have an agreement with the EU are clear that these talks are purely technical exercises aimed at replicating as far as possible the effects of current trade agreements to ensure continuity.</p><p>It will be possible at a future date to update any agreement with the agreement of both partners.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819141/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T12:13:27.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819141/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819141/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-01-09","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, with reference to his oral contribution of 9 January 2018, on the Trade Bill, if he will list the countries which have indicated an interest in negotiating a new trade agreement with the UK after the UK leaves the EU where those countries have an existing agreement with the EU.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","121818"
