"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819143","Department for International Trade","false","2018-01-17","<p>I refer the hon Member for Sefton Central to the answer I gave on 20 November 2017 no. <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-11-14/112931/" target="_blank">112931</a>.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819143/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T12:32:35.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819143/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819143/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-01-09","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if he will list those countries with which the EU has a trade agreement which he intends to form the basis for a new trade agreement with UK.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","121820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819144","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-15","<p>The answer to Question 120488 by my honourable friend, the member for East Surrey, sought to make clear that detached duty is driven by operational decisions and assessments based on a wide range of information. The discrete data that HMPPS currently collates in relation to detached duty is designed for administrative use only, to assist and support the management of detached duty. In the broadest terms it relates to staffing levels and demand and supply levels of available staff.</p><p> </p><p>The data is drawn from a number of sources and it is necessarily dynamic and often time limited with a number of caveats. The data and a number of other dynamic dependencies are brought together in the context of the need at a particular time when detached duty is being planned and implemented. At present, there is no intention to routinely publish such data relating to detached duty.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819144/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:23:47.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819144/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819144/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-09","Prison Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 8 January to Question 120488, for what reasons that Answer did not provide information on what categories of information the Government collects on detached duty.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","121821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819145","Department for International Trade","false","2018-01-17","<p>Our priority is to secure continuity of the existing trade arrangements as we leave the EU, to provide certainty and stability for businesses, consumers and investors. After leaving the EU, we will be able to operate our own independent trade policy - negotiating new trade agreements with third countries.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819145/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T13:22:37.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819145/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819145/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-01-09","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, with reference to his oral contribution of 9 January 2018, on the Trade Bill, what plans he has made for the potential renegotiation of any existing EU trade agreements into UK law after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","121822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819146","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-17","<p>Through our Embassy in Baghdad and Consulate-General in Erbil we consistently urge the Government of Iraq and the Kurdistan Regional Government to ensure the safe, voluntary and unhindered return of all Internally Displaced Persons, including Yazidis, supported by the prospect of genuine community reconciliation. I raised this issue with the Iraqi Prime Minister’s Office during my visit to Iraq in September 2017 and the Prime Minister did so with Prime Minister Abadi during her visit to Iraq on 29 November 2017. Ensuring that all Iraqis are able to return to their homes safely will be critical to post-conflict stabilisation efforts.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819146/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T16:36:11.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819146/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819146/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-01-09","Yazidis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with the Iraqi government on measures to assist Yazidi refugees to return to their homes.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","121823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819147","Department for International Trade","false","2018-01-17","<p>The GPA mutually opens procurement markets, providing opportunities worth around £1.3 trillion globally each year. There is no consistent data on the total value of procurement contracts won by UK businesses or foreign companies across all GPA members. The Trade Bill Impact Assessment gives the value of direct contract awards to UK businesses within the EU which are covered by the GPA. This averaged £609 million per year (across 2014 and 2015). The GPA also provides protection for UK subsidiaries set up in GPA Parties by ensuring they cannot be discriminated against on the basis of foreign affiliation.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819147/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T11:59:00.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819147/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819147/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-01-09","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what the total level of earnings was of UK businesses from Government Procurement Agreements (GPA) in each of the last five years; and what the total level of earnings by foreign companies from such GPAs was in that period.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","121824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819148","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-15","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and can only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819148/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:30:27.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819148/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819148/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-09","Reoffenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate his Department has made of the number of people losing custody of children following their recall to prison in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","121825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819149","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-01-16","<p>We will convert existing EU law into UK law when we leave through the EU Withdrawal Bill. We will put in place measures to implement this legislation nationally, including arrangements to replicate the functions carried out by any European bodies where these are still needed in a national regime.</p><p> </p><p>We will continue to have an evidence based approach to pesticides regulation when we leave the EU, with the aim of achieving a high level of protection for people and the environment.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819149/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T14:04:20.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819149/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819149/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-01-09","Pesticides: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what measures his Department has put in place to replicate the functions of the European bodies responsible for regulating pesticides in preparation for the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","121826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819150","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-15","<p>Some £450,000 was paid to prison staff in damages in 2016/17 who had brought personal injury claims following alleged assaults.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819150/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:34:05.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819150/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819150/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-09","Prisons: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much was paid from the public purse in compensation to prison staff as a result of injuries suffered in a violent attack on the prison estate in the most recent financial year for which such information is available.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","121827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819151","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-01-16","<p>Like all departments, Defra is planning for a number of scenarios following our departure from the EU to make sure we are ready on Day 1. Over £250 million of additional funding has already been approved across a number of departments in 2017/18 to prepare for when we have left the EU. Defra has received additional funding this year and has reprioritised to meet new pressures arising from preparations for withdrawal from the EU. The additional funding received from the Reserve for 2017/8 will be set out at Supplementary Estimates.</p><p> </p><p>As our design and implementation of the UK pesticide regulation regime continues, we will continue to work alongside HM Treasury to keep our resource needs under review. It has committed to working with departments through 2017/18 and into 2018/19 to take forward necessary plans.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819151/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T13:34:04.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819151/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819151/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-01-09","Pesticides: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what additional funding has been put in place to create a new pesticide regulatory system after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","121828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819152","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-01-16","<p>We set out our plans for pesticides in the 25 Year Environment Plan:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/673203/25-year-environment-plan.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/673203/25-year-environment-plan.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819152/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T13:30:14.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819152/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819152/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-01-09","Pesticides: Monitoring","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans he has to implement the recommendation of his Department's Chief Scientific Advisor to create a system to monitor how pesticides affect the environment at a landscape scale.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","121829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819153","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-15","<p>HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service expenditure on agency staff is published each year in their annual report and accounts.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=hm-courts-and-tribunals-service&amp;publication_type=corporate-reports" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=hm-courts-and-tribunals-service&amp;publication_type=corporate-reports</a></p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819153/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:58:23.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819153/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819153/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-09","HM Courts and Tribunals Service: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 20 December to Question 119017, how much HM Courts and Tribunal Service has spent on agency staff pay in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","121830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819154","Department for International Trade","false","2018-01-17","<p>Our priority is to secure continuity of the existing trade arrangements as we leave the EU, to provide certainty and stability for businesses, consumers and investors.</p><p>All the countries which currently have an agreement with the EU are aware that this is a purely technical exercise aimed at replicating as far as possible the effects of current trade agreements to ensure continuity.</p><p>After leaving the EU, the UK will be able to implement an independent trade policy. This would make it possible to revisit and improve existing agreements where appropriate.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819154/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T11:43:50.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819154/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819154/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-01-09","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, with reference to the oral contribution of the Minister of State for International Trade on 9 January 2018, if he will publish a definition of what constitutes a significant change to existing trade agreements; and if he will list those countries that have indicated an interest in changing existing such agreements.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","121831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819155","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-17","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could be obtained only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819155/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T17:26:11.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819155/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819155/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-09","Prisoners: Childbirth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many women in each prison establishment gave birth in 2017.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","121832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819156","Department for Education","false","2018-01-15","<p>A decision was made not to continue development of the Early Years Investment Fund in order to ensure resources are being directed to where there is the greatest need.</p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819156/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:52:55.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819156/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819156/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-09","Pre-school Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, for what reason the Early Years Investment Fund has been closed.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","121833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819157","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-16","<p>Local Overseas Allowance is paid to cover the additional local day to day living costs of service personnel when serving overseas. The current rates of Local Overseas Allowance for Main Stations are attached. Rates are updated periodically to reflect changes to currency exchange rates which affect the Forces Fixed Rate. I am withholding information regarding the rates of Local Overseas Allowance for Small Stations as its disclosure would prejudice commercial interests and release information provided in confidence.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819157/answer","Main Stations.pdf","Main Stations.pdf","121834 - MOD Local Overseas Allowance","121834 - MOD Local Overseas Allowance",,"2018-01-16T16:21:17.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819157/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819157/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-09","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library a copy of the Living Overseas Allowance for each station.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","121834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819158","Department for Education","false","2018-01-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on 27 November 2017 to Questions 114905, 114907 and 114908:</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=114908" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=114908</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819158/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:52:48.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819158/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819158/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-09","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many (a) childminders and (b) group-based childcare settings rated (i) good and (ii) outstanding by Ofsted in each local authority have left the Early Years Register in each month of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","121835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819159","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-15","<p>The adjuvanted trivalent influenza vaccine was not available for use in 2017/18.</p><p> </p><p>General practitioners (GPs) and pharmacies are responsible for ordering and purchasing flu vaccines for the adult seasonal flu programme (eligible individuals aged 18 years and over) directly from manufacturers.</p><p> </p><p>Information on what vaccines are being ordered by these independent contractors is not routinely collected. Information on vaccines used by pharmacies and GPs will be available after the end of a flu season when practice/pharmacies claim reimbursement for the cost of the vaccines they have used.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819159/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:50:12.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819159/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819159/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-09","Influenza: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the take-up of the new enhanced influenza vaccine for the over-65s by (i) GPs and (ii) pharmacies in the  2017-18 and 2018-19 influenza seasons.","true","Biography information for Sir Kevin Barron","Rother Valley","Sir Kevin Barron","121836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819160","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-15","<p>Public Health England has updated their advice in the Green Book chapter on influenza so that clinicians are aware of the advice of the Joint Committee on Vaccination and Immunisation in relation to the adjuvanted trivalent influenza vaccine.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, NHS England wrote to general practitioners and clinical commissioning groups (via NHS England local teams) in December 2017 to provide an update on the use of the adjuvanted trivalent influenza vaccine for 2018/19.</p><p> </p><p>This update will also be made available to community pharmacies as part of confirming that the Advanced Influenza Vaccination service has been recommissioned in early 2018. Community pharmacies are able to order relevant vaccines as detailed in the service specification, including the enhanced vaccine for patients within the relevant cohort.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819160/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:47:39.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819160/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819160/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-09","Influenza: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans he has to encourage the take-up of the new enhanced influenza vaccine for the over-65s for the 2018-19 influenza season with GPs and pharmacies.","true","Biography information for Sir Kevin Barron","Rother Valley","Sir Kevin Barron","121837"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819161","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-15","<p>Officials at the Department and Public Health England have regular discussions with manufacturers on a range of issues. This has included discussion with Seqirus, the company that has produced the new adjuvanted trivalent flu vaccine (aTIV).</p><p> </p><p>Officials have had no discussions with general practitioner representatives or patient groups on the aTIV.</p><p> </p><p>Officials also attend meetings of the Joint Committee on Vaccination and Immunisation, which includes a lay member.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819161/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T17:51:33.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819161/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819161/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-09","Influenza: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what discussions he has had with representatives from (a) GPs, (b) patient organisations and (c) manufacturers on the availability of the new enhanced influenza vaccine for the over-65s for the 2017-18 and the 2018-19 season.","true","Biography information for Sir Kevin Barron","Rother Valley","Sir Kevin Barron","121838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819162","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-15","<p>There are currently 61 ports operating in the UK which the Department for Transport classifies as ‘minor’ for the purposes of the statistics it gathers.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819162/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-15T12:22:40.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819162/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819162/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-09","Ports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many minor ports across the UK are currently in operation.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","121839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819163","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-17","<p>The illicit supply of drugs undermines the safety and security of prisons. We are taking urgent and decisive action tackle those behind this criminal enterprise.</p><p> </p><p>In 2017, the prison with the largest weight of drugs found was HMP Hindley with a total drug weight of 13.6kg seized.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819163/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T17:54:07.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819163/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819163/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-09","Prisons: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, in which prison was the largest weight of drugs was found in 2017.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","121840"
