ures, and the determination of prison staff to disrupt this behaviour.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819164/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-17T17:55:06.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819164/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819164/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-09","Prisons: Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many mobile phones or sim cards were found in each prison in 2017.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","121841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819165","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-16","<p>Ports in the United Kingdom operate on a commercial basis. They have an excellent track record of investment in new and improved facilities and I see no reason why this should change. The Government fully recognises the vital role ports play in our transport infrastructure through facilitating trade and promoting economic growth and accordingly engages regularly with a wide range of ports as well as their representative bodies.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819165/answer",,,,,,"2018-01-16T15:20:03.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819165/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/819165/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-09","Ports: Modernisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he plans to take to modernise UK ports.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","121842"
